# Given ColorectalCancer(x) → BileDuctCancer(x) and the above rule, it implies:

# Since we know ColorectalCancer(x) implies BileDuctCancer(x), this means:

∀x (ColorectalCancer(x) → ¬LowSurvivalRate(x))

# Conclusion:
( ( IsA(ColorectalCancer, BileDuctCancer) ∨ Cholangiocarcinoma(ColorectalCancer) ) → ( IsA(ColorectalCancer, BileDuctCancer) ∧ MildFlu(ColorectalCancer) ) )
